	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=item.html?item=21420&mid=105781381234221>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=item.html?item=21420&mid=105781381234221>Do a little more research...</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=21420&mid=105781381234221#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Jul 10th 1:19 AM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=193324><span id= >Akephalos</span></a><br><span id=notbold>1 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The beastlord order was named after the Vah Shir hero. That hero's name was Khati Sha, and according to the lore, he was one of the founding fathers and a great explorer. <br><br>At some point during his exploration, he was captured by the Shissar, who attempted to turn him into a demi-god. That experiment went horribly wrong, Khati Sha was twisted and demented and ended up tearing up a bunch of Shissar, after which he lost all memory of what he is, and what he was, so he wandered Luclin rather aimlessly untill he happened upon a set of caverns. <br><br>These caverns, what we have come to know as Acrylia Caverns, were largely uninhabited, except for a few odd beings. With his powers, he propogated those beings, and created the entire race of grimlings.<br><br>The Compass of Khati Sha fits in nicely with the story, since he was an adventurer, it would make sense that he have a compass. It would also make sense that at some point during his transformation, he lost it. It is not out of the realm of possibility that he lost it in the caverns, nor is a grimling finding it.<br><br>That easily ties together the reason why it doesn't drop from Khati Sha, and could be an explanation as to why it's not usable by beastlords. He is no longer a beastlord, nor does he have any recollection of his legacy. <br><br>As far as the &quot;exceptionally bad piece of story&quot;, that's largely false, the story makes a great deal of sense, once you actually do some decent research. The revamp with acrylia actually tied up a lot of luclin unknowns.<br><br>I'm a lore nut, it's one of my favorite things about the game. Most of this information can be dug up by posts on the Beastiary section of the site, as well as the safehouse (some 13 page thread there about Acrylia.)<br>--Ake<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Jul 10 01:19:58 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
